Here's a modification of the `load` and `save` methods to use chunk reading and writing, in order to reduce memory usage and improve performance:
```php
    private function load() {
        $handle = fopen($this->file, "r");
        while (!feof($handle)) {
            $chunk = fread($handle, 1024); // read 1024 bytes at a time
            $rows = explode("\n", $chunk);
            foreach ($rows as $row) {
                $record = json_decode($row, true);
                if (!empty($record)) {
                    $id = $record["id"];
                    $this->records[$id] = $record;
                }
            }
        }
        fclose($handle);
    }

    private function save() {
        $handle = fopen($this->file, "w");
        foreach ($this->records as $record) {
            $data = json_encode($record) . "\n";
            fwrite($handle, $data);
        }
        fclose($handle);
    }
```
